    <h1>Yonathan Mendenhall</h1>
    <h2>Anaheim, California</h2>

    <p>Hey there! I'm a 24-year-old currently in my second year of school, majoring in Computer Science. My passion for technology runs deep — ever since I was a kid, I’ve loved building and understanding how things work.</p>

    <p>At 14, I launched my first project: an online simulation game that used MariaDB to handle users' login information. That was the beginning of my journey into backend development and data management.</p>

    <p>At 15, I started my own side business unlocking and jailbreaking iPhones — back when that was popular. It gave me early entrepreneurial experience and hands-on technical skills.</p>

    <p>I got my first associate role as a Copy Center Tech at Keystone Property Management. That experience changed how I view the corporate world. It helped me realize how much I want to grow professionally, keep learning, and make an impact.</p>

    <p>Today, I’m passionate about tech and driven to grow within a company that values development. My long-term goal is to become a <strong>Data Analyst</strong>, where I can blend my love for data, problem-solving, and technology to create meaningful insights.</p>

